text: Urbino is an Italian city in Marche, southwest of Pesaro, a World Heritage Site with a great cultural history during the Renaissance as the seat of Federico da Montefeltro, duke of Urbino from 1444 to 1482. The University of Urbino is in Urbino. In 2019, 14,106 people lived there. Category:Cities in Pesaro and Urbino Category:World Heritage Sites in Italy
title: Urbino
